  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This unit evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use scope — identifying worst-case hemolysis operating points for adult CPB flows between 3–6 L/min at 1750–3500 RPM — is described in the bound requirement and claim text. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case-cpb",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-gcbp-piv-experimental-2013",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-bench-2021"
  ],
